# Multi-Platform Rules (多平台适配)

ScrollCap targets iOS 17+, iPadOS 17+, macOS 14+. Every feature MUST work on all three.

## File organization

```
App/Shared/     → Cross-platform code (majority of views/services)
App/iOS/         → iOS/iPadOS-only (IOSCaptureView, FrameReader, etc.)
App/macOS/       → macOS-only (MacCaptureView, MenuBarView, OverlayWindow, etc.)
```

## Platform guards

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - compile-time guard for platform-specific APIs
#if os(macOS)
    NSSavePanel()
#elseif os(iOS)
    UIPasteboard.general
#endif

// ✅ GOOD - runtime device check for iPad vs iPhone
if UIDevice.current.userInterfaceIdiom == .pad {
    NavigationSplitView { ... }
} else {
    TabView { ... }
}
```

## Environment injection

Every window/scene MUST inject the full environment chain:

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - complete for ALL scenes
WindowGroup {
    ContentView()
        .environment(appState)
        .environment(\.userMode, appState.userMode)
        .applyUserMode(appState.userMode)
}

// macOS-specific scenes ALSO need full injection:
Settings {
    SettingsView()
        .environment(appState)
        .environment(\.userMode, appState.userMode)
        .applyUserMode(appState.userMode)
}
MenuBarExtra("ScrollCap", systemImage: "camera.viewfinder") {
    MenuBarView()
        .environment(appState)
        .environment(\.userMode, appState.userMode)
        .applyUserMode(appState.userMode)
}

// ❌ BAD - Settings/MenuBarExtra DON'T inherit from WindowGroup
Settings { SettingsView().environment(appState) }  // missing userMode!
```

## iPad-specific

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - inject PadMetrics for iPad
if UIDevice.current.userInterfaceIdiom == .pad {
    splitView.environment(\.platformMetrics, PadMetrics())
}

// Available metrics: PhoneMetrics (default), PadMetrics, MacMetrics
// Key differences: sidebarWidth, minContentWidth, capturePreviewMaxWidth
```

## macOS-specific

- macOS `Settings` scene has its own window — inject ALL environments
- `MenuBarExtra` window is separate — inject ALL environments
- Use `.frame(minWidth:minHeight:)` on sheets/panels for reasonable macOS sizing
- Support keyboard shortcuts via `.keyboardShortcut()`

## Shared views best practices

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - platform-adaptive in shared view
var body: some View {
    #if os(macOS)
    content.frame(minWidth: 350, minHeight: 300)
    #else
    content
    #endif
}

// ✅ GOOD - use PlatformMetrics for adaptive layout
@Environment(\.platformMetrics) private var metrics
.padding(metrics.defaultPadding)
.frame(maxWidth: metrics.capturePreviewMaxWidth)
```

## Checklist for new features

- [ ] Works on iOS (iPhone), iPadOS, and macOS
- [ ] Platform-specific APIs guarded with `#if os()`
- [ ] iPad gets `PadMetrics` environment (wider sidebar, bigger previews)
- [ ] macOS sheets have `.frame(minWidth:minHeight:)`
- [ ] All window scenes inject complete environment chain
- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts added for macOS where appropriate
